summary: Former Little Mix star Perrie Edwards revealed she has never lived with her fiancé, footballer Alex Oxlade-Chamberlain, despite being in a relationship for eight years and having a son together. In an interview, she shared that she almost quit Little Mix due to emotional distress but was persuaded to stay by her manager. Edwards' solo projects mark a new chapter in her career, following her successful tenure with Little Mix.

name: Bluey
summary: Bluey, the popular children's animated series, has sparked various headlines related to its future and recent developments. Amidst rumors of its cancellation, the producer has confirmed that more episodes are in the works, easing concerns among fans. Additionally, a new and emotional episode has drawn attention for its transformative impact. An exclusive Bluey toy range is now available at Aldi, bringing joy to parents with its affordable prices. While some parents have expressed concerns about the show's possible ending, the creators have assured its continued production. Fans have also noticed an Easter egg connection to Doctor Who in a recent episode. Interestingly, Bluey has listed its iconic house for sale, marking a potential shift in the show's setting. Despite some backlash and threats of boycotts due to its alleged emotional impact on children, Bluey remains a beloved and highly-rated series among both young viewers and their parents.

name: Houghton Hall
summary: A new exhibition by artist Antony Gormley, titled "Time Horizon," has been installed at Houghton Hall in Norfolk, England. The display features 100 life-sized sculptures placed throughout the stately home's grounds, creating an immersive and interactive experience reminiscent of the "Where's Wally?" books. Gormley describes the exhibition as a reflection on his own mortality and his desire to create a work that would exist beyond his lifetime. The sculptures serve as a commentary on Brexit, which Gormley sees as a "self-harm" for the United Kingdom. The exhibition also includes works by other artists inspired by climate change. One such work, by Rose Hanbury, the Marchioness of Cholmondeley, has received attention for her handwritten thank-you note to a fan who sent her a birthday gift.

name: Fallout 4
summary: Fallout 4, the popular post-apocalyptic role-playing game from Bethesda, is still receiving updates and attention nearly seven years after its release. The game's developers, Bethesda, recently announced that Fallout 4 is receiving free updates, including a next-gen update that will enhance the game's graphics and performance on newer consoles. The update, which includes various patch notes and improvements, has a confirmed release date and will also make Fallout 4 Steam Deck Verified, ensuring a smooth gaming experience on the portable device. The continued support for Fallout 4 has sparked renewed interest in the game, with many gamers revisiting the post-apocalyptic wasteland.
